customUI.walkthrough.welcome.title = Welcome to Simple Enchantments!
customUI.walkthrough.welcome.desc = This mod allows you to enhance your gear and weapons using magical scrolls and enchantments. It is highly customizable, featuring an admin configuration menu (/enchantconfig) that lets you tweak settings or toggle specific enchantments on and off. It works best with vanilla items, but it offers broad compatibility with other mods. If you encounter an issue or have a feature request, please join our Discord server. Additionally, if Dynamic Tooltips Lib is installed, enchantments will be shown in the item tooltip.

customUI.walkthrough.table.title = 1. The Enchanting Table
customUI.walkthrough.table.desc = Craft an Enchanting Table at the Workbench. Place it down and interact with it to browse all available Enchantment Scrolls that you can craft. You can also upgrade the table to access higher tier enchantments.

customUI.walkthrough.scrolls.title = 2. Enchantment Scrolls
customUI.walkthrough.scrolls.desc = Craft scrolls directly at the Enchanting Table using essences, gems, ingots and plants. Once crafted, right-click the scroll while holding it to apply the enchantment to a weapon, armor, or tool in your inventory. Scrolls have different rarities, showing how strong or unique the enchantment is. Most enchantments have 3 Levels, but there are some exceptions. Legendary enchantments are especially strong or unique. You can also combine or upgrade scrolls. Just select another scroll instead of a Item when applying enchantments and the scrolls will be combined.

customUI.walkthrough.removing.title = 3. Removing Enchantments
customUI.walkthrough.removing.desc = Made a mistake? You can craft a Cleansing Scroll to strip off enchantments from an item. On this server, you {returnScroll} get the scroll back.

customUI.walkthrough.salvaging.title = 4. Salvaging
customUI.walkthrough.salvaging.desc = If you have an enchanted piece of gear that you no longer need, place it in the Salvaging Station to retrieve the highest tier enchantment scroll if enabled on the server.

customUI.enchantingPage.adminNote = Server-wide settings and Enchantment customizations are available in the Admin Config. Access it via /enchantconfig


customUI.walkthrough.enchantments.title = 5. Enchantments
customUI.walkthrough.enchantments.desc = A complete list of enchantments and their effects. Click on any to find out more. On this Server, each Item can have up to {maxEnchantments} Enchantments.\n\nNote: Right now each enchantment page only shows the Tooltip description of the enchantment and if it is enabled on the sever. I plan to write detailed descriptions for each of them, but that takes time. Each future update to the mod will add a detailed description and to some of them.

